data.name: Herb-Crusted Pork Chops with Roasted Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Honey-Glazed Brussels Sprouts
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy pork chops encrusted with fresh herbs, paired with creamy garlic-infused mashed potatoes and sweet, caramelized Brussels sprouts.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix the chopped rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, salt, and pepper with 2 tablespoons of olive oil to form a paste.
Rub the herb mixture generously over both sides of the pork chops.
Heat a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon of olive oil.

Sear the pork chops for about 4-5 minutes on each side until golden brown. Transfer the skillet to the oven and roast for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145°F (63°C).
While the pork chops are cooking, boil the cubed potatoes in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes. Drain and return to the pot.
Add the roasted garlic (sautéed in the same oven as the pork), butter, and cream to the potatoes. Mash until smooth and creamy. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
For the Brussels sprouts, toss them with honey, salt, and pepper. Spread them on a baking sheet and roast in the oven alongside the pork for the last 20 minutes until caramelized and tender.
To serve, plate the pork chops with a generous scoop of roasted garlic mashed potatoes and a side of honey-glazed Brussels sprouts.
